Sandra E. Peterson

Group Worldwide Chairman / Johnson & Johnson



posted Nov 14th, 2013 at 8:43pm 









 




 Comments 











Sandra E. Peterson

Sandra E. Peterson is Group Worldwide Chairman, Johnson & Johnson, and member of the company’s Executive Committee. She has responsibility for the Consumer Group of Companies, Information Technology, and Global Supply Chain. Prior to joining the company in December, 2010, she had an extensive global career in life sciences, consumer goods, and consulting.
Sandi previously served as Chair and CEO of Bayer CropScience AG, based in Europe, a role she assumed in 2010 after serving as president and CEO of Bayer Medical Care and president of Bayer HealthCare AG’s Diabetes Care.
Prior to joining Bayer in 2005, Peterson spent five years in leadership roles at Medco Health Solutions (formerly Merck-Medco). She also led global research and development, procurement and regulatory affairs at Nabisco, Inc., and strategy, finance and product development at Whirlpool Corporation. She began her career in consulting, with McKinsey & Company, Inc.
A graduate of Cornell University with a B.A. in government, Sandi also holds an M.P.A. in Applied Economics from Princeton University. She is a member of the board of directors of The Dun & Bradstreet Corporation.
 






